main event: A UFO was reported in Syracuse, New York, on 14 February 1955, described as a round, bluish-white object seen hovering in the sky.
interesting points: The object was observed by USAF personnel and remained stationary for 25-30 minutes., The observation took place at approximately 3,000 feet altitude directly overhead., Witnesses described the object as similar to a fluorescent light bulb., There was no physical evidence or photographs documented in the report., The report concluded that the object's nature was unknown.
